cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper deals with unsupervised learning of representations from a stream of data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of a Self-Taught Associative Memory (STAM) module is a novel approach to this problem, and the evaluation of the STAM representations involves clustering and classification tasks, which are common in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of online clustering, novelty detection, and forgetting outliers suggests a potential connection to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
